General Motors Corp said it orderedtemporary layoffs of 5,500 hourly workers to cut production andthereby reduce inventories of cars built at two plants laterthis month.    A spokesman said 2,000 workers would be laid off one weekbeginning March 9 at GM's Detroit-Hamtramck luxury car plant.    Another 3,500 will be laid off a week effective March 23 atGM's Lansing, Mich, plant which builds the company's "N-body"compact cars. Reuter&#3;